---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Safety & Etiquette — Buffalo Drinking Game">
  <section class="py-12 md:py-16">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4">
      <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-extrabold text-buffalo-dark text-center mb-3">
        Real Talk: Safety First
      </h1>
      <p class="text-center text-buffalo-gray mb-10 max-w-lg mx-auto">
        Buffalo is legendary because it's fun. It stops being fun the second
        someone feels pressured, unsafe, or uncomfortable. Don't be that person.
      </p>

      <div class="space-y-6 mb-12">
        <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-xl p-6">
          <h2 class="font-bold text-xl text-buffalo-dark mb-3 flex items-center gap-2">
            <span class="w-3 h-3 rounded-full bg-buffalo-success inline-block flex-shrink-0"></span>
            Someone says they're done? They're done.
          </h2>
          <p class="text-buffalo-gray leading-relaxed">
            No "just one more." No guilt trips. No calling them soft.
            Everyone drinks at their own pace. Buffalo is fun because it's
            social — not because it forces anyone to do anything.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-xl p-6">
          <h2 class="font-bold text-xl text-buffalo-dark mb-3 flex items-center gap-2">
            <span class="w-3 h-3 rounded-full bg-buffalo-success inline-block flex-shrink-0"></span>
            Buffalo is always opt-in
          </h2>
          <p class="text-buffalo-gray leading-relaxed">
            You can only get Buffalo'd if you agreed to play. You can't
            draft someone into this game against their will. If they don't want
            to play, that's the end of the conversation. Move on.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-xl p-6">
          <h2 class="font-bold text-xl text-buffalo-dark mb-3 flex items-center gap-2">
            <span class="w-3 h-3 rounded-full bg-buffalo-success inline-block flex-shrink-0"></span>
            Non-alcoholic drinks always count
          </h2>
          <p class="text-buffalo-gray leading-relaxed">
            Not drinking? You can still play. Water, soda, coffee — all fair
            game for Buffalo. The game is about the hand, not what's in it.
            Never make someone feel excluded for choosing not to drink.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-xl p-6">
          <h2 class="font-bold text-xl text-buffalo-dark mb-3 flex items-center gap-2">
            <span class="w-3 h-3 rounded-full bg-buffalo-success inline-block flex-shrink-0"></span>
            The penalty is optional. Seriously.
          </h2>
          <p class="text-buffalo-gray leading-relaxed">
            Got Buffalo'd but don't want to chug? That's your call. The
            penalty makes the game fun, but it should never feel like an
            obligation. Good groups have lighter penalty options. Be a good group.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-xl p-6">
          <h2 class="font-bold text-xl text-buffalo-dark mb-3 flex items-center gap-2">
            <span class="w-3 h-3 rounded-full bg-buffalo-success inline-block flex-shrink-0"></span>
            Know your local laws
          </h2>
          <p class="text-buffalo-gray leading-relaxed">
            Legal drinking age varies everywhere. This site is for adults of
            legal drinking age only. Know the rules where you are. We're not
            lawyers and this isn't legal advice — just common sense.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-xl p-6">
          <h2 class="font-bold text-xl text-buffalo-dark mb-3 flex items-center gap-2">
            <span class="w-3 h-3 rounded-full bg-buffalo-success inline-block flex-shrink-0"></span>
            Look out for your people
          </h2>
          <p class="text-buffalo-gray leading-relaxed">
            Someone's had too much? Get them water. Get them a ride. Be there.
            The best Buffalo players know when to call "Buffalo" and when to
            call it a night. That's not weakness — that's the real game.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-buffalo-warning/10 border border-buffalo-warning/30 rounded-xl p-6 text-center">
        <p class="font-bold text-buffalo-dark text-lg mb-2">
          Drink responsibly. No exceptions.
        </p>
        <p class="text-buffalo-gray text-sm">
          If you or someone you know is struggling with alcohol, help is available
          right now. Call the SAMHSA National Helpline at
          <a
            href="tel:1-800-662-4357"
            class="text-buffalo-primary font-medium hover:underline"
          >
            1-800-662-4357
          </a>
          — free, confidential, 24/7.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
